net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.data

Class AbstractTableModel

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.data.AbstractTableModel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TableModel
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BaseDataColumnTableModel, MutableCellTableModel, ResultSetTableModel, SQLTableModel, TableMap

    public abstract class AbstractTableModel
extends java.lang.Object
implements TableModel

    Implements most methods of TableModel with decent values. Provides common listener/event methods. The only methods that need to be provided when extending this class are getColumnCount(), getValueAt() and getRowCount().

    Author:
    Pat B. Double (double@i2rd.com)

      • fireTableStructureChanged

        public void fireTableStructureChanged()
        Notifies all listeners that the table's structure has changed. This includes not only the data but the columns of the table. This method will normally result in the component that is using the model to reconstruct the ColumnModel, thereby removing all properties set by the application.

      • getRowId

        public java.lang.String getRowId(int rowIndex)
        Returns null.

        Get an unqiue ID for the row. This ID will be used in some mediums to find the row in the case where the model and user interface become inconsistent. When accessing the table model, the ID may be used to find the row index.

        This method may return null if not supported.

        Specified by:
        getRowId in interface TableModel
        Parameters:
        rowIndex - The row index.
        Returns:
        String or null if no ID is available.

      • isRowValid

        public boolean isRowValid(int rowIndex)
        This implementation of isRowValid() returns true if the rowIndex is in the interval [0,getRowCount()). Returns true if the row is valid in this model. In general a row should be valid if it is less than the value of getRowCount(). Determining getRowCount() may not be efficient for all models so this method is provided to determine if a given row is valid. It is assumed that if a row is invalid, all the rows with an index greater than the row checked are also invalid.
        Specified by:
        isRowValid in interface TableModel
        Parameters:
        rowIndex - The row index.
        Returns:
        true if the row is valid.
